<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
As male, except for the following character states: Eyes dichoptic (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 79–82" captionStartId="F30" captionText="Figures 79 - 82. Mesembrius spp., head, frontal view 79 M. simplicipes Curran (♂) 80 M. sulcus sp. nov. (♀) 81 M. tarsatus (Bigot) (♀) 82 M. vockerothi sp. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures79-82" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557491" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">82</figureCitation>
). Frons white pilose, brown pilose on ocellar triangle and surrounding area; strongly white pollinose to just before ocellar triangle. Pile on legs shorter. Abdomen as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 124–126" captionStartId="F38" captionText="Figures 124 - 126. Mesembrius spp., abdomen, dorsal view 124 M. sulcus sp. nov. (♀) 125 M. tarsatus (Bigot) (♀) 126 M. vockerothi sp. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures124-126" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557499" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">126</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
